description.narrative:
1. Alignment of sector budget allocations to priorities set out in sector plans and aligned to GoSS's stated development priorities

2. Enhanced capacity of staff within the Aid Management Directorate to monitor donor projects & development of aid management system;

3. Increased capacity of SSCCSE to produce, use and monitor socio-economic statistics to measure progress on MDGs

comment.narrative:
1. 10 Government of Southern Sudan Budget Sector Working Groups in place with 3 year plans from 2009-2011.   Weak planning and linkages with state/county public financial management system; 

2. Aid strategy approved and being implemented but aid information database not yet in place; Capacity constraints for staff within  Directorate of Aid Coordination;

3. MDG report has never been produced for Southern Sudan; Limited use of socio-economic statistics to collect and monitor information on MDGs

1. 30 (15 female) persons with access to legal aid, and legal services through MoJ and CBOs
2. Additional 100 social workers and 100 police personnel (50% female) in five states; 
3. ECC established and operational in Wau and Juba ECC operational;
4. 50% of eligible personnel issued with Police identity cards
